Okay, I got it.

```
type RemoveUndefinable&lt;T&gt; = {
  [Key in keyof T]: undefined extends T[Key] ? never : Key
}[keyof T]; //--&gt; that&#39;s lookup
```

So, say we have a type 
```
type MyType = {
  id: number;
  name: string;
  property?: string;
}
```
RemoveUndefinable&lt;MyType&gt; produces
```
{
  id: &quot;id&quot;
  name: &quot;name&quot;
  property?: never
}[&quot;id&quot; | &quot;name&quot; | &quot;property&quot;] // &quot;id&quot; | &quot;name&quot; | undefined
```
And this
```
MyType[RemoveUndefinable&lt;MyType&gt;]
```
is equivalent to
```
MyType[&quot;id&quot; | &quot;name&quot; | undefined]
```

