You need to prefix your `class` name with a `dot` in `JS`. So if your class is named as `select2`, your code instead of 

````
        jQuery(&#39;select2&#39;).select2({
            theme: &quot;classic&quot;
        });
````

should be

````
        jQuery(&#39;.select2&#39;).select2({ //See the Dot
            theme: &quot;classic&quot;
        });
````

In the HTML that you shared, your select has class `order-statuses`. So JS to initialize `select2` would be 


````
    jQuery(&#39;.order-statuses.).select2();
````

